cragInfo.name: Niagara glen
cragInfo.restrictions: Top Roping Ban, The Park's current policy is that there should be NO ROPED CLIMBING going on at all in the Glen. This is NOT limited to the headwall. This includes: Super Flywall, Flywall, The Fly Part III, The Cube, The O Boulder, and the Stucco Walls. Please Respect this ban and leave the ropes at home.

directions.copy: Take the QEW Niagara to the 405 (Towards Queenston). Before going over the Lewiston-Queenston bridge, get off onto Niagara Parkway south (turn right) towards Niagara Falls. Niagara Glen will be on your left about 5 Km.

Take the I-190 north from Buffalo over Grand Island. Go into Canada over the Lewiston-Queenston bridge. Immediately after paying the toll, exit onto Niagara Parkway (on your right). Proceed south (turn right off the exit) for approximately 5Km. The Glen will be on your left.

sectorClimbs.name: Ruffneck
sectorClimbs.description: Starts about 5 feet left of Orient express on a rounded sidepull edge/pinch for the left and a positive sidepull flake/edge for the right. Move though over hang using sidepull edges, a 2/3 finger pocket, and a large gaston. Finish directly above the 2/3 finger pocket on a 2 finger slot pocket and an incut crack pinch

sectorClimbs.name: Rigormortis
sectorClimbs.description: Start sitting as for Ruffneck. Go out right to a sidepull and then fall into a jug undercling pocket. Right hand to an intermediate crimp, and then bump into the Orient Express crimp. Slap a two-finger sloping divot and follow the lip to the topout.

sectorClimbs.name: Orient Express
sectorClimbs.description: Start on the softball sized scoop pocket. Move up using edges, shoot to the lip pocket and again to another pocket. Finish up and right on large edges.

sectorClimbs.name: OG Pockets
sectorClimbs.description: Start sitting with hands in shallow but positive four finger slot pockets. Move up and left thru positive pockets, end on very good "organic" pockets.

sectorClimbs.name: Original Gankster
sectorClimbs.description: Same start as for "OG pockets", but head out right, using a low pocket out right then crossing above to another pocket. Pull the lip using pockets and edges. Top it out.

sectorClimbs.name: Nogoko
sectorClimbs.description: Overing hanging line that is harder than it looks. Start both hands on large holds below the prow. Cross with right to pocket/pinch up high move left to edge, then pull lip. Harder at top than appears.

sectorClimbs.name: Sibishi
sectorClimbs.description: Start on a sharp crimp with the left and a scoop undercling with the right. Move up the face matching on a crimp rail then snatching another crimp up and left. Finish on the obvious Jug-rail at the top.

sectorClimbs.name: Peewee
sectorClimbs.description: Sitdown start to the right of Sibishi. Left hand on sidepull flake just to the right of undercling pocket. Right hand on a crimpy sidepull ( Itlooks like a little ear). Fall back onto another sidepull near your face before throwing for the long crimp edge. Match it and finish as Sibishi.

sectorClimbs.name: Carpet Munching Diablos
sectorClimbs.description: Climb the blank face on the left side of the boulder.

sectorClimbs.name: Ko-Chi-Minh-Trail
sectorClimbs.description: Start in the middle of the boulder on a couple of bad crimps. Right hand on a gaston and left hand on a right leaning crimp. Go with your right hand to a sharp left leaning crimp. This hold brings you into an iron cross. Work your way on few bad holds to eventually make a toss to the good edge just before the top of the boulder. Top out.

sectorClimbs.name: Pegasus
sectorClimbs.description: Start left hand in pocket under lip, right hand on square cut sloper. Use the foot underneath. Move up and right on small but positive crimps. Finish on the horizontal crack.

sectorClimbs.name: Horseshack's Reprise
sectorClimbs.description: Climb the small edges and pockets near the right arete to the top.

sectorClimbs.name: Gateway
sectorClimbs.description: Start on the two-sided jug, crank up right to your choice of small, but-positive holds, latch the undercling then slap-throw to the big pocket on the slopey ledge. Stay right of the small seam.

sectorClimbs.name: Discman
sectorClimbs.description: Start on the far left side on a crimp and large sidepull. Traverse right until you can drop down to an undercling. Follow the seam up.

sectorClimbs.name: Real Kung-Fu Massacre
sectorClimbs.description: Good right hand edge to a gaston and then up.

sectorClimbs.name: Bluetips
sectorClimbs.description: Climb the left most line on this prominent face following an incipient crack to its flaring end.

sectorClimbs.name: Beast Man
sectorClimbs.description: start 3 ft left of the right side of boulder on a big sidepuu/underpull move to the inverted v pinch and move through micro pockets to the top jug.

sectorClimbs.name: STD "Barnes"
sectorClimbs.description: This is the first face you see before you hike up the slope. If you look close you'll see "STD" carved into the rock. Start off a left hand pinch(right next to the STD), right hand on a side pull. Climb up and over the buldge and onto the blank slab face via grimps, pockets, and will power. Then make the slap for the angled topout.

sectorClimbs.name: And My Fish . . . Grew Legs
sectorClimbs.description: Start on the right side of the main face under the obvious line of weakness. Climb the crack and flakes to the top.

sectorClimbs.name: Naturally Selected
sectorClimbs.description: Start directly left of 'And My Fish . . . Grew Legs'(right hand is on start holds). Move straight up to the 4 in. hueco about 10 ft up. Then pop to the top. It is a straight line up through the hueco to the top.

sectorClimbs.name: Existencialistic
sectorClimbs.description: On the center of the face to the right of the vertical crack, start on the obvious undercling to the left of the obviosly dangerous undercling. Stay out of the vertical crack. Move up left to the overhanging arete until you can find the large ledge above. TO not suggested.

sectorClimbs.name: I Love Barbie
sectorClimbs.description: It starts in the cave on two apposing sidepulls and then goes to a small two finger pocket. Then out to a slopey rail continue up through crimps and pockets to topout.

sectorClimbs.name: Ken Lost His Nuts
sectorClimbs.description: This problem starts on the right side of the boulder, under the cave, on two opposing sidepulls with feet underneath. Move up right to a slopey/shallow pocket with bomber tumb catch, and then out left to a postive but crimpy rail. Finish through pockets to large block and topout.

sectorClimbs.name: Beef Baron
sectorClimbs.description: Start on the bottom left side. After the first undercling pocket climb small crimps to the top.

sectorClimbs.name: The Real Bruce Lee
sectorClimbs.description: An old projy. Start crouched right of Kung fu, left hand low on a bad sloper and right hand higher on a better sloper. Climb up the face on slopey crimps, then a big move to a V-notch. After that, big sidepulls to the topout. Arete is off for hands and feet. Technical.

sectorClimbs.name: Josh's Highball
sectorClimbs.description: Climb Dumbass and head up above the finsh on somesidepulls and edges. Head up and left on terrible slopers to a dicey heel hook last move. Top out.

sectorClimbs.name: Tales of Power
sectorClimbs.description: Start on the block. Move left through small pockets around the arete to the finish pocket. Topout on the slab.

sectorClimbs.name: Life O'Rielly
sectorClimbs.description: Start on sloper crimps head high. Crank up and left to sloper rail. Fire for crimps and top out. Variation 1: (V7) Sit down, grab super low holds and crank into Life...

sectorClimbs.name: No U-Turn
sectorClimbs.description: Start on the holds on the left side of the right face. Crank up to the small V-notch. Then out right and up to finish. Variation 1: (V2) Match on the ledge right of the v-notch, and dyno for the top.

sectorClimbs.name: Felcher
sectorClimbs.description: Climb the left arete. Tallman starting holds

sectorClimbs.name: Electric French Fries
sectorClimbs.description: Climb up the center of the vertical wall along the trail. Variation 1: (V6, SD) Start sitting down. Move up and left, then back right to join normal route. Variation 2: (V6, SD) Direct start to the normal problem.

sectorClimbs.name: Slow Frowns in Brown Town
sectorClimbs.description: Start on the blocky overhung side of the boulder visible from Danzig. Go up using underclings,some crimps, and some pockets, topout.

sectorClimbs.name: Hook Direct
sectorClimbs.description: Start under the roof on some side pulls. Crank out to the normal start holds of Captain Hook.

sectorClimbs.name: The Phoenix
sectorClimbs.description: Start low in the middle of the Captain Hook cave matched on a left facing scouped edge. Work up and right thru underclings, flat slaps, and pinches. Top out to the left of the Captain Hook start holds. Nice.

sectorClimbs.name: The Crucifix
sectorClimbs.description: Starts 2 metres left of Phoenix at the same height. Start on 2 underclings. Use crimps and flat holds to go up and right. A huge ironcross move takes you to a pocket at the lip of the bulge. cross over into jug and top out just to the left of the phoenix top out.

sectorClimbs.name: Traverse
sectorClimbs.description: Starting on the left side of the back face, follow the low large ledges.

sectorClimbs.name: Standard
sectorClimbs.description: Climb the obvious flake.

sectorClimbs.name: Left
sectorClimbs.description: Start on the blank face left of the flake. Using edges, crank straight up.

sectorClimbs.name: Pot Mouth
sectorClimbs.description: Start on the obvious rail in the middle of the boulder. Climb straight up.

sectorClimbs.name: Pistol Pete
sectorClimbs.description: Start in the very back of the cave. Use the roof holds and climb out and up.

sectorClimbs.name: Yosemite Sam
sectorClimbs.description: Start in the back of the cave on the left & climb out.

sectorClimbs.name: Stickley's High Step
sectorClimbs.description: Start on holds on the arete directly next to the stairs. Cruise through the high step to the top.

sectorClimbs.name: Brian's Got a Rubber Toy
sectorClimbs.description: Start under the roof for a direct start to Bolero. Move to the monster lock off on crimps, and move to the big jug. Finish as for Bolero.

sectorClimbs.name: Crimp-de-la-Crimp
sectorClimbs.description: Start on the jug under a roof and the hold directly above, through foot out to to ledge on right, pull the lip and crimp on small pockets to the top. Downclimb and jump!!

sectorClimbs.name: Dad's Day Out
sectorClimbs.description: Start to the right of Plumbers Crack underneath the roof on the obvious holds. Crank out to the face and over the lip.

sectorClimbs.name: Pinch a Loaf
sectorClimbs.description: On the left side of the face, a crack splits the boulder. Start right side of crack (left side off), left hand on crimp, right on large pinch. Move up and thru a series of crimps and pinches to a jug, careful on top out.

sectorClimbs.name: Band Saw
sectorClimbs.description: Starts 3ft. left of log jam. Start left hand on a sharp crimp (You'll Know!) right hand on sidepull (1 ft. below two finger pocket that's off). Move up and left to sidepull, then to a sloping hold just left of the crack, finish by traversing way left thu a slot and other large holds. Hard start, SCARY TOPOUT.

sectorClimbs.name: Log Jam
sectorClimbs.description: Found on the right corner of face, where the log ends. Place your ass on the log and bear hug to side pulls. Crank up to a large sloping rail (with friendly spots), finish via slabing top corner.

sectorClimbs.name: Elevated Bloc a.k.a. The Flesh Prince
sectorClimbs.description: This problem is around the corner from the other 3 problems .your back should be towards the phoenix. start standing at two underclings, climb over the bulge using crimps and sidpulls, and bomb for crimp up and left, top out with big jugs

sectorClimbs.name: Cream Cheese
sectorClimbs.description: On the face that is facing Cal's boulder is a ramp that angles right. Jump into the hole and start here. Use the tweaky crimpers to access a slopey pinch and a triangle flake. Topout to the left of that.
sectorClimbs.restrictions: Be sure to stay off the lip on either side!!

sectorClimbs.name: Dognuts
sectorClimbs.description: Start on the left side, follow the seam lines all the way to the top.

sectorClimbs.name: General Principles
sectorClimbs.description: Traverse the main face staying low. Move left to right. Finish on the big sidepull around the corner.

sectorClimbs.name: V2by2
sectorClimbs.description: Start in the middle of the main face. Move to the huge undercling, dyno to a small edge then finish.

sectorClimbs.name: Elephant Talk
sectorClimbs.description: Start on the far right side, 2 feet left of the arete. Climb the crimpy small edges all the way to the top.

sectorClimbs.name: Poo-Tips
sectorClimbs.description: Start on the jugs under the hang, reach out for the crimpy edge, throw right to the slopy side-pull, end on the obvious ledge.

sectorClimbs.name: Walking Spanish Down the Glen
sectorClimbs.description: THE Classic V0 in the Glen. Slap both sidepulls and cruise up the arete all the way to the top.

sectorClimbs.name: The Icey Heel
sectorClimbs.description: Start down low and heel hook your way up the corner. Finish on the right side.

sectorClimbs.name: Vigilante Justice
sectorClimbs.description: On the backside of this boulder is a mini cave. There is a waist high boulder in the landing. The problem starts low in the overhang on a fat pinch for the left and a bad right hand crimp. Climb up the overhang using some cool slopers and then rocket to the jug at the lip. Topout left in the clean jugs.

sectorClimbs.name: Floating Seagulls
sectorClimbs.description: Start on the 2 handed jug. Move left to the arete and traverse onto the face and gain the big jug to the topout.

sectorClimbs.name: Cocina
sectorClimbs.description: Start with left hand on a big sidepull edge right hand of the lowest opposing sidepull, bump up to sidepull and launch for the jug of Floating Seagulls then topout.

sectorClimbs.name: A Cry For Deliverance
sectorClimbs.description: Direct SD to Cocina. Start sitting left hand on small crimp sidepull, right hand slopey sidepull. Climb up more well-spaced sidepulls into Cocina's start, and finish on Cocina.

sectorClimbs.name: Bone Jumper
sectorClimbs.description: Start on the right arete of the overhanging face on 2 slopers. Move up to fat pinch, then through pockets to the top.

sectorClimbs.name: The Magic Bullet
sectorClimbs.description: Start on a low sidepull and the left pocket. Move up to the right pocket, then to the lip. Topout.

sectorClimbs.name: Quickie
sectorClimbs.description: Start near the left side of the overhanging face on the huge flake. Move left to the big pocket, then far right back to the lip. Topout through the weeds.

sectorClimbs.name: Banana Soup
sectorClimbs.description: Start on the small edges down low on the left side. Crank up through a series of small edges to the sidepull flake and finish.

sectorClimbs.name: Hat with no Tassle
sectorClimbs.description: Start down low on the big pockets in the middle of the boulder. Pull up to a small edge and go for the bucket above.

sectorClimbs.name: Cheez Itz
sectorClimbs.description: Start under a cool roof. Crank out the roof using holds up and right. Dyno over the roof to finish.
